2026-06-09 22:53:28,798 DEBUG Tool call: submit_final_result({'final_result': '## Principal Valuation, Underwriting, and Allocation Decisions Not Yet Finalizable\n\nBecause the preliminary SpaceX S-1 (filed May 20, 2026) leaves the offering price range, share count, and key fee terms as blank placeholders, institutional investors cannot yet finalize the following decisions:\n\n---\n\n### I. VALUATION DECISIONS\n\n| Decision | Filing Status | Impact on Institutional Investors |\n|----------|--------------|-----------------------------------|\n| **IPO price per share** | Blank on cover page ("$ [__] to $ [__]") | Cannot determine entry valuation, price-to-sales or price-to-earnings multiples, or compare to last private-market round (SpaceX Series N at $270/share pre-split; xAI Series E at $75.46/share) |\n| **Post-IPO market capitalization** | Derivable only after pricing | The SEC fee table registers maximum aggregate offering prices from $5.5T to $7.5T for 66,666,670 shares, but the actual implied equity value depends on the final price × total shares outstanding (pre-IPO baseline: ~6.93B Class A + ~5.60B Class B after the 5-for-1 split and preferred conversion) |\n| **Per-share dilution to new investors** | Dilution table structure present; all dollar values blank | Investors cannot calculate the gap between the IPO price and the pro forma net tangible book value per share (as of March 31, 2026), which determines the immediate accounting dilution they will absorb |\n| **Total consideration & ownership split** | Sensitivity framework disclosed ("each $1.00 increase/decrease…") but base figures blank | Cannot model the percentage of total equity capital contributed by new investors vs. Elon Musk and existing shareholders, or the average price per share each group has paid |\n| **Valuation milestone context** | xAI merger performance awards tied to 12 milestones from $1.065T to $6.565T | Without the IPO price, investors cannot assess whether the offering prices the company above or below these internal performance hurdles |\n\n---\n\n### II. UNDERWRITING DECISIONS\n\n| Decision | Filing Status | Impact on Institutional Investors |\n|----------|--------------|-----------------------------------|\n| **Underwriting discounts & commissions** | Per-share and total amounts blank in the fee table | Cannot calculate net proceeds to the company, which affects use-of-proceeds modeling (including mandatory SpaceX Bridge Loan repayment within six months) and the effective cost of capital |\n| **Dealer concession per share** | Blank ("a concession not in excess of $ [__] per share") | Selling-group members and their institutional clients cannot determine the economics of participating in the distribution |\n| **Over-allotment (greenshoe) share count** | Blank ("up to [__] additional shares") | Cannot model potential supply overhang, post-IPO price stabilization capacity, or the full dilutive impact if the option is exercised in full |\n| **Final syndicate allocation** | Managing underwriters named (Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley, BofA, Citigroup, J.P. Morgan + ~15 additional firms), but individual allocation percentages not disclosed | Institutional investors cannot determine which bookrunner controls their allocation or assess potential conflicts (many syndicate members are also lenders under the SpaceX Bridge Loan and Credit Facility; Morgan Stanley advised on the xAI acquisition) |\n| **FINRA expense reimbursement cap** | Blank | Affects the total offering-expense estimate and, therefore, net proceeds |\n| **Discretionary account limit** | Stated as not to exceed 5% of total shares offered | The absolute share count subject to this cap cannot be calculated without the final offering size |\n\n---\n\n### III. ALLOCATION DECISIONS\n\n| Decision | Filing Status | Impact on Institutional Investors |\n|----------|--------------|-----------------------------------|\n| **Total shares offered** | Blank on cover page ("We are offering [__] shares"); fee table implies 66,666,670 shares across pricing tiers | Cannot determine the size of the investable opportunity or the public float as a percentage of total equity |\n| **Directed Share Program reservation** | Percentage blank ("reserved [__]% of shares") | Reduces the shares available to the general institutional book; without the percentage, investors cannot estimate how tight the institutional allocation will be |\n| **Retail investor access allocation** | Platforms named (Schwab, Fidelity, Robinhood, SoFi, E*TRADE) but share quantities not specified | Cannot assess the retail-vs-institutional split, which affects expected first-day demand dynamics and price volatility |\n| **Final public float & index eligibility** | Depends on offering size and price | Cannot determine whether the post-IPO float will meet thresholds for S&P 500, Nasdaq-100, or Russell 1000 inclusion, which drives passive-fund demand |\n| **Lock-up overhang timing** | 366-day lock-up for Musk (100% of his shares, no early-release provisions); 180-day lock-up for other insiders with early-release triggers tied to earnings releases | While the structure is known, the absolute number of shares that will become freely tradable at each unlock date depends on the final capitalization table, which is price-dependent |\n| **Registration rights exercise** | Holders of a specified (but blank) aggregate of Class A shares possess registration rights under an Investors\' Rights Agreement | Cannot model potential secondary supply from early investors who may exercise demand or piggyback registration rights post-lock-up |\n\n---\n\n### IV. SUMMARY OF CRITICAL UNKNOWN VARIABLES\n\nInstitutional investors require the following finalized data points—expected in the 424(b) pricing amendment—to complete their investment decision:\n\n1. **IPO price per share** (and the filed price range)\n2. **Number of shares offered** (base deal size)\n3. **Over-allotment option size** (greenshoe shares)\n4. **Underwriting discount/commission per share** (and total)\n5. **Dealer concession per share**\n6. **Directed Share Program percentage**\n7. **Pro forma net tangible book value per share** (as of March 31, 2026, adjusted)\n8. **Resulting dilution per share to new investors**\n9. **Post-IPO shares outstanding by class** (Class A and Class B)\n10. **Estimated total offering expenses**\n\nUntil these blanks are filled, institutional investors cannot finalize their valuation models, position-sizing decisions, allocation requests, or secondary-market trading strategies for SPCX on Nasdaq/Nasdaq Texas.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026)"\n    }\n  ]\n}'})
